column5: Heade to the shack this afternoon àround 3 and fished till 5.Only had one hour of great action but muskie came in and spooked walleyes out.just one here and there for last hour.Did hook into tge muskie and she peeled about 50 yards off my reel.I got her back slowly bùt ended up breaking me off.fun though.weathercreal decent here.To warm in shack with heat on.got frost out and turned it off.walleyes on bottom where not interested in tge bait only the ones at 12 ft would bite.headed out tomorrow for lake trout and hear there is a lot of slush on the laķes now.not enough ice and now to much snow.èdward lake has no slush on road to shack.
John I will be pissed off if the northern n muskies scare away my dinner, but if I have to go toe to toe with those big boys I will,rod
That road to the shack looks better than the roads here Rochester mn hahaha
Its very well maintained.lol. Thx bill been a good gig there so far.
